<div id="top-bar">
	<div class="back"><div class="fill"></div></div>
	
	<div class="logo">
		<div class="graphic">
			<img alt="OrgClut" src="images/logo.orgclut.wh-tr.276x83.png"/>
		</div>
		<h1 class="text">OrgClut</h1>
	</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<h2 class="tagline"><span class="imp">Org</span>anize your <span class="imp">Clut</span>ter.</h2>
	</div>
</div>

<div id="page">
	
	<div id="flashes">
		<% if flash[:message]: %><span class="flash message"><%= flash[:message] %></span><% end %>
		<% if flash[:notice]: %><span class="flash notice"><%= flash[:notice] %></span><% end %>
		<% if flash[:warning]: %><span class="flash warning"><%= flash[:warning] %></span><% end %>
		<% if flash[:error]: %><span class="flash error"><%= flash[:error] %></span><% end %>
	</div>
	
	<div id="schpiel">
		<h3 class="leader"><span class="sym">∴</span>The Easy, Open-Ended Way To Organize All Your Cluttered:</h3>
		<h4><ul>
			<li>thoughts</li>
			<li>ideas</li>
			<li>errands</li>
			<li>assignments</li>
			<li>projects</li>
			<li>or whatever else…</li>
		</ul></h4>
	</div>
	
	<div id="feature-box">
		
		<div class="screenshot">
			<img alt="[OrgClut screenshot]" src="images/screenshot.pile-view.2009-10-07.960x893.png"/>
			<div id="fill" class="initially-hidden"></div>
			<%#img class="overlay n1 initially-hidden" alt="[OrgClut screenshot]" src="images/screenshot.pile-view.2009-10-07.960x893.png"/>
			<img class="overlay n2 initially-hidden" alt="[OrgClut screenshot]" src="images/screenshot.pile-view.2009-10-07.960x893.png"/>
			<img class="overlay n3 initially-hidden" alt="[OrgClut screenshot]" src="images/screenshot.pile-view.2009-10-07.960x893.png"/%>
		</div>
		
		<ul id="features">
			<li class="feature n1" onclick="void(0);">
				<div class="inner">
					<h3>Hierarchical</h3>
					<p><strong>OrgClut is limitless.</strong><br/>All your notes are part of your own personal <em>“Pile”</em>, a deeply nested list of items and sub-Piles. Easily “scope” into your Piles to see just what's relevant, while keeping an eye on the bigger picture.</p>
				</div>
			</li>
			<li class="feature n2" onclick="void(0);">
				<div class="inner">
					<h3>Powerful</h3>
					<p><strong>OrgClut gives you more.</strong><br/>You're free to attach text, check boxes, priorities, labels, links, dates/times, media, etc. anywhere in your Pile. Then find what you need by sorting and filtering, and share what you want with who you want.</p>
				</div>
			</li>
			<li class="feature n3" onclick="void(0);">
				<div class="inner">
					<h3>Flexible</h3>
					<p><strong>OrgClut is made for you.</strong><br/>“Projects”, “Contexts”,  are not assumed, but you're free to organize it that way if you wish. Therefore, you can use it for GTD, SCRUM, or own methodology. <em>“GTD 2.0”, anyone?</em></p>
				</div>
			</li>
		</ul>
		
		<div class="clear"></div>
		
	</div>
	
</div>


